26/1: venezuela
1. What Happened (Confirmed Developments in the first 3 days of 2026)
• U.S. forces conducted a large-scale military operation in Caracas, Venezuela’s capital, capturing President Nicolás Maduro and his wife, Cilia Flores. The raid involved elite U.S. special forces and airstrikes targeting Venezuelan military sites. 
• Maduro and Flores were flown to the United States and appeared in federal court in New York on charges including narco-terrorism and cocaine trafficking, part of a superseding indictment unsealed after their capture. 
• The U.S. government has indicated it may maintain influence over Venezuelan policy and secure access to Venezuela’s vast oil resources. 
• The legality of the operation is under intense international scrutiny; critics including the UN Secretary-General describe it as setting a dangerous precedent under international law. 
• Allies of Venezuela such as China have condemned the action as “unilateral bullying” and a violation of sovereignty. 
• Switzerland has frozen assets linked to Maduro and associates in response to the arrests. 

