5/2: Writing task 1
the given line chart depicts different causes of contaminant from 1990 to 2005 in the UK
Overall, air pollution such as households and industry tended to decrease significantly. Meanwhile, population from transport had an up trend.
Especially, in 1990, total air pollutants peaked at approximately 7 million tonnes.

Regarding industrial pollution, a clear downward trend can be seen. In 1990, emissions stood at approximately 7 million tonnes, before declining steadily over the period to about 3 million tonnes in 2005.
Meanwhile, pollution from transport increased slightly at first before decreasing towards the end of the period. 
In contrast, household emissions remained relatively low throughout, finishing at under 2 million tonnes.

